' =====================================================================
'  ScholarPath — UML Component & Deployment diagram.
'  Clean-Architecture monolith on Azure. Gap-analysis D1-D9 closed:
'   D1 Hangfire annotated «optional» (feature-flagged)
'   D2 SsoService -> Google + Microsoft OAuth shown
'   D3 key-provider ports split (field-encryption & JWT via their own providers)
'   D4 OpenAI-direct AI/embedding provider shown
'   D5 recommendations annotated as Local-AI driven
'   D6 email config switch (SMTP / dev stub)
'   D7 Power BI = embed tokens only (no reverse-ETL implemented in this codebase)
'   D8 ASP.NET Identity surfaced inside the API
'   D9 IMemoryCache shown («planned: Redis»)
' =====================================================================
@startuml ScholarPath_Components
title ScholarPath — component & deployment diagram
skinparam componentStyle uml2
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam ranksep 50
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #F7F8FC
  BorderColor #3F4A5A
}

node "Azure Static Web Apps" as SWA {
  [React 19 SPA] as SPA
}

node "Azure App Service (Linux) — monolith" as APPSVC {
  [Web API\n(controllers + Stripe webhook receiver)] as API
  [ASP.NET Core Identity\n+ JWT Bearer] as IDN
  [SignalR Hubs\nChat · Notification · Community] as HUBS
  [Hangfire Jobs\n«optional · Hangfire:Enabled»] as JOBS #FFFDE0
  [Application\n(CQRS + ports + AiCostGate)] as APP
  [Domain\n(entities · enums · events)] as DOM
  [Infrastructure\n(adapters implementing ports)] as INF
  [IMemoryCache\n«planned: Redis»] as CACHE #FFFDE0
}

cloud "Azure data, AI & messaging" as AZ {
  database "Azure SQL" as SQL
  [Azure OpenAI\n(gpt-4o-mini + embeddings)] as AOAI
  [Azure Comm. Services\n(video + recording)] as ACS
  database "Blob Storage" as BLOB
  [Key Vault] as KV
  [Event Hub] as EH
  [Power BI] as PBI
}
[OpenAI direct\n(chat + embeddings)] as OAI
[Stripe\n(PaymentIntents · Connect)] as STRIPE
[SMTP mail / dev stub] as SMTP
[ClamAV] as CLAM
[Google OAuth] as GOOG
[Microsoft OAuth] as MSFT

' client -> server
SPA --> API   : HTTPS / REST + JWT
SPA ..> HUBS  : WebSocket
API --> IDN

' inward (Clean Architecture) dependencies
API  --> APP
HUBS --> APP
JOBS --> APP
APP  --> DOM
INF  ..> APP  : implements ports
INF  --> DOM
APP  --> CACHE

' infrastructure -> external systems
INF --> SQL
INF --> AOAI   : chat + embeddings
INF --> OAI    : alt provider (Ai:Provider)
INF --> ACS
INF --> BLOB   : Storage:Provider
INF --> CLAM   : FileScanning:Enabled
INF --> KV     : field-key + JWT-key providers
INF --> EH
INF --> SMTP   : Email:Provider
INF --> STRIPE : create / capture / refund
INF --> GOOG   : SSO
INF --> MSFT   : SSO
STRIPE --> API : webhook
EH  --> PBI
PBI --> API    : embed tokens

note bottom of INF
  Recommendations are produced by the deterministic LocalAiService
  (offline metadata scoring + RAG); Azure/OpenAI back the chat & Q&A only.
  Key Vault is reached via IFieldEncryptionKeyProvider and IJwtKeyProvider.
end note
@enduml
